Date: 5 Oct 2000 12:11:25 GMT
From: M. Cosgriff <mcosgriff@hotmail.com>
Source: Straits Times, 3 Oct 2000 [edited

Hand, Foot & Mouth disease Spreads to Older Children
----------------------------------------------------
SINGAPORE: Hand, foot and mouth disease appears to have spread to older
children with at least one kindergarten confirming an unspecified number of
cases and another being investigated. The kindergarten with clinically
confirmed cases of the disease is Bethesda Pasir Ris Kindergarten. A
statement from the Ministry of the Environment (ENV) yesterday said that it
had been "alerted of a possible cluster of [cases of hand, foot and mouth
disease at YWMA Kindergarten (Bukit Batok Centre)", but it had yet to
confirm if the children were actually ill with the disease.
Meanwhile, there have been another 43 clinically diagnosed cases at
child-care centers, bringing the total since last week to 165 cases. And
the number of child-care centers with infected children is now 28. However,
many of the sick children have now recovered. So far, 58 of them have been
certified fit by their doctors, said an ENV spokesman.
[Byline: Salma Khalik
