Date: 5 Oct 2000 13:42:18 GMT
From: M. Cosgriff <mcosgriff@hotmail.com>
Source: Yahoo Asia News, 5 Oct 2000 [edited

Thirteen New Suspected Cases of Hand, Foot & Mouth Disease Admitted to
Hospital
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
SINGAPORE: A total of 13 new cases of clinically suspected hand, foot and
mouth disease (HFMD) have been admitted to the isolation wards at KK
Women's and Children's Hospital (KKH) and National University Hospital
(NUH). This brings the total hospitalized cases to 33, all of them mild
cases in stable condition.
Since HFMD was made legally notifiable on 1 Oct 2000, 229 cases have been
reported. In a daily update of the situation, the 4 ministries involved in
the HFMD taskforce said that of the 27 cases reported to be in hospital on
Tue 3 Oct 2000, 7 have been discharged.
The 5-year old child, whose siblings are suspected to have died from HFMD,
is now out of intensive care.
